<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-428-608  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 428 608.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  July 10 1989 v6 n27 p8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Low-cost software scans images into CAD systems. (American ImagingServices Inc., computer-aided design) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Levin, Karen.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Imaging Services Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   LunaTrace (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionScanningSoftware PackagesComputer-Aided DesignImage Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Low-Cost Software Scans Images into CAD SystemsandM;CARROLLTON, Texas -- American Imaging Services has introduced a low-costscanning software program that works with users' existing CAD equipment toscan images into their CAD system.andM;Priced at $79.95, LunaTrace accepts scanned images from any optical scannerthat supports a PCX file of as much as 900 square inches and coverts it to aDXF file.andP;  It is then loadable by any CAD system with a DXF function.andM;&quot;It's a program that does the conversion and builds the file, then you canload the image of that original drawing right into your CAD system,&quot; saidCharles Read, vice president of American Imaging Services.andM;Companies can use existing CAD equipment or a service bureau to scan images.andO;Amercian Imaging Services will scan images onto a floppy diskette for $10.andM;Only 512KB of memory is required for LunaTRace.andP;  VAX/VMS users need aDOS-based machine or window with a DSX file on a DEc machine.andP;  &quot;They have todo the translation on a DOS machine or in a DOS window,&quot; said Read.andP;  &quot;Some ofthe systems have DOS windows even though they're using a Unix or VMSmachine.&quot;andM;Because LunaTrace uses straight line vectors, there is some loss ofresolution.andP;  For $2,000, American Imaging Services offers the LunaSeries, aset of program modules that works with raster data and will handle any sizedrawing.andM;For additional information, American Imaging Services Inc. can be contactedat 2315 Luna Road, Carrollton, TX 75006, (800) 234-7226.andO;</TEXT></DOC>